<emphasis bold="true" box="[556,620,1658,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">17–18</emphasis>
. Male genitalia: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[792,824,1658,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">17.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug, 1832)" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1832" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[830,1168,1658,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pachyanthrax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circe">
<emphasis box="[830,1029,1658,1680]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Pachyanthrax circe</emphasis>
(Klug, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
, lateral; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1256,1287,1658,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Greathead, 1970)" authorityName="Greathead" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Greathead" baseAuthorityYear="1970" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pachyanthrax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nomadorum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Pachyanthrax nomadorum</emphasis>
(Greathead, 1970)
</taxonomicName>
, lateral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1749,2026]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis box="[199,261,1751,1774]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Note:</emphasis>
This is the first record of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[719,790,1751,1775]" name="Egypt" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Egypt</collectingCountry>
. Its specimens were included in a series of 
<emphasis box="[1275,1436,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evenhuis" authorityYear="1978" box="[1275,1376,1749,1774]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Veribubo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Veribubo</taxonomicName>
anus
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wiedemann" box="[158,366,1785,1810]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" refString="Wiedemann, C. R. W. (1828) Aussereuropaische zweiflugelige Insekten. Als Fortsetzung des Meigenschen Werkes. Erster Theil. Schulz, Hamm, xxxii + 608 pp." type="book" year="1828">Wiedemann, 1828</bibRefCitation>
) amongst many other bee flies that were loaned to the British bee fly taxonomist late Dr. John Bowden (died in 2012) from the main Egyptian insect collections. Some specimens are labeled with hand written labels by Dr. Bowden as “ 
<emphasis box="[441,632,1857,1882]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">
<taxonomicName box="[441,625,1857,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifiacies">Villa albifiacies</taxonomicName>
”
</emphasis>
; he might have identified them using 
<bibRefCitation author="Engel" box="[1055,1205,1857,1882]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" refString="Engel, E. O. (1937) Bombyliidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. 4 (3). (25). E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 561 - 619." type="journal article" year="1937">Engel (1937)</bibRefCitation>
; however, the famed British bee fly taxonomist late Dr. David Greathead (died in 2006) checked these specimens and commented to me (personal communication) that they appear to be 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Greathead" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[719,1021,1929,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pachyanthrax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nomadorum">
<emphasis box="[719,1021,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Pachyanthrax nomadorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He agreed with me that specimens that were identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1840" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1840" box="[413,809,1965,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifacies">
<emphasis box="[413,622,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Anthrax albifacies</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Macquart" box="[630,809,1966,1990]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" refString="Macquart, P. J. M. (1840) Dipteres exotiques nouveaux ou peu connus. Tome Premier. 1 re Partie. N. E. Roret, Paris, 131 pp. [pp. 5 - 135]" type="book chapter" year="1840">Macquart, 1840</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lioy" authorityYear="1864" box="[1146,1198,1965,1990]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Villa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1146,1198,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Villa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Engel" box="[1244,1393,1965,1990]" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" refString="Engel, E. O. (1937) Bombyliidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. 4 (3). (25). E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 561 - 619." type="journal article" year="1937">Engel (1937)</bibRefCitation>
are conspecific with his species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Greathead)" authorityName="Greathead" baseAuthorityName="Greathead" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[469,914,2001,2026]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Pachyanthrax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nomadorum">
<emphasis box="[469,769,2001,2026]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="508">Pachyanthrax nomadorum</emphasis>
(Greathead)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
